1
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:01,770
EPISODE 13

2
00:02:01,454 --> 00:02:03,331
It's not cold! It's not!

3
00:02:03,414 --> 00:02:05,959
It's hot! It's really hot!

4
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:12,173
One, two.

5
00:02:19,556 --> 00:02:20,557
You're up.

6
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:24,727
I left the restaurant just fine.
Did I black out?

7
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:27,397
Yes. I guess you're not much of a drinker.

8
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,440
I usually only drink a glass of wine.

9
00:02:29,524 --> 00:02:31,818
-Are you okay?
-I am.

10
00:02:32,318 --> 00:02:33,903
I'm a little…

11
00:02:33,987 --> 00:02:36,656
I think you loosened up
after we left there.

12
00:02:36,739 --> 00:02:38,867
The alcohol suddenly hit you.

13
00:02:38,950 --> 00:02:40,910
That happens, you know.

14
00:02:40,994 --> 00:02:44,205
You were blacking out,
so I escorted you into my car right away.

15
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:45,999
I'm sorry.

16
00:02:46,082 --> 00:02:49,669
No, I should be the one who's sorry.
Had I known you couldn't drink,

17
00:02:49,752 --> 00:02:52,672
we would've had just a little…
No, we wouldn't have drunk at all.

18
00:02:52,755 --> 00:02:55,842
My tolerance must've gotten lower.
It wasn't this low.

19
00:02:57,260 --> 00:03:00,388
I'm sorry. Were you jumping around outside
because of me?

20
00:03:00,471 --> 00:03:02,599
It's okay. I just worked out.

21
00:03:03,349 --> 00:03:05,018
I was out here for about 40 minutes.

22
00:03:05,101 --> 00:03:07,061
My goodness. What time is it?

23
00:03:09,647 --> 00:03:10,940
It's not even 10 p.m.

24
00:03:12,609 --> 00:03:14,360
Your face is frozen.

25
00:03:14,444 --> 00:03:16,529
What if you got frostbitten?

26
00:03:20,074 --> 00:03:21,367
Come up for a bit.

27
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:24,579
You should have some hot tea.
You could get really sick.

28
00:03:27,749 --> 00:03:29,459
-Hurry up.
-What?

29
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:31,169
But…

30
00:04:06,579 --> 00:04:08,081
Poor you.

31
00:04:08,164 --> 00:04:09,624
It's okay.

32
00:04:09,707 --> 00:04:12,794
You should've woken me up
even if you had to slap me.

33
00:04:12,877 --> 00:04:14,963
Thanks to you, I'm totally sober now.

34
00:04:17,298 --> 00:04:18,466
Come on in.

35
00:04:19,050 --> 00:04:21,344
Gosh, I forgot to use honorifics.

36
00:04:21,427 --> 00:04:23,137
I'm much younger than you.

37
00:04:23,972 --> 00:04:25,306
It won't take long.

38
00:04:25,848 --> 00:04:26,808
Okay.

39
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:31,062
I have beef porridge. Would you like some?

40
00:04:31,145 --> 00:04:32,855
Jumping around made me hungry.

41
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:34,816
You need to warm your body.

42
00:04:34,899 --> 00:04:37,568
We didn't eat a lot for dinner.

43
00:04:37,652 --> 00:04:40,321
-Let me take this off.
-Sure.

44
00:04:41,781 --> 00:04:45,118
Regardless of who it belongs to,
a home is always wonderful.

45
00:04:45,201 --> 00:04:47,161
I feel bad for those who don't have one.

46
00:04:47,245 --> 00:04:49,372
I need to wash my hands.

47
00:04:49,455 --> 00:04:51,624
Right. The bathroom is over there.

48
00:05:07,473 --> 00:05:09,183
-Have a seat.
-Thanks.

49
00:05:13,396 --> 00:05:16,691
It's already seasoned,
but do you still need kimchi?

50
00:05:16,774 --> 00:05:18,568
I prefer to have it on its own.

51
00:05:18,651 --> 00:05:21,195
Me too. I don't like it
when the two flavors are mixed.

52
00:05:22,322 --> 00:05:24,615
-Stir it first.
-Right.

53
00:05:26,784 --> 00:05:28,828
I hope you don't get sick.

54
00:05:28,911 --> 00:05:31,372
You could catch a cold
staying outside like that.

55
00:05:31,456 --> 00:05:33,833
All I did was work out at night
after a good meal.

56
00:05:36,919 --> 00:05:38,254
Thank you for the food.

57
00:05:43,259 --> 00:05:44,302
It's good.

58
00:05:44,802 --> 00:05:46,637
I've never had beef porridge before.

59
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:49,640
Really? Do you not like porridge?

60
00:05:49,724 --> 00:05:52,935
I do, but I usually had
abalone porridge and soybean porridge.

61
00:05:53,019 --> 00:05:54,562
My dad likes soybean porridge.

62
00:05:54,645 --> 00:05:57,356
I've never had soybean porridge before.

63
00:06:06,574 --> 00:06:08,534
This is warming up my body.

64
00:06:08,618 --> 00:06:11,412
My sister-in-law gave me
some tangerines from Jeju Island.

65
00:06:11,913 --> 00:06:13,623
You should have them yourself.

66
00:06:20,171 --> 00:06:22,840
-I have plenty.
-Thank you.

67
00:06:24,884 --> 00:06:28,179
-You don't have to do it now.
-It's okay.

68
00:06:35,603 --> 00:06:38,231
The more I eat it,
the more savory it gets.

69
00:06:38,314 --> 00:06:40,066
There's no sugar, but it's sweet.

70
00:06:40,691 --> 00:06:43,611
Anything your body wants tastes sweet.
Oh, my.

71
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:46,239
You're not okay, are you?

72
00:06:46,322 --> 00:06:49,367
I'm not feeling nauseous,
but I'm a bit woozy.

73
00:06:49,450 --> 00:06:50,326
How do you feel?

74
00:06:51,828 --> 00:06:53,246
I feel bad.

75
00:06:53,329 --> 00:06:56,499
When you blacked out, I was really scared.

76
00:06:56,582 --> 00:06:58,126
I wanted to go to the hospital,

77
00:06:59,168 --> 00:07:00,920
but you looked so peaceful.

78
00:07:01,504 --> 00:07:03,673
It seemed like you were having
a sweet dream.

79
00:07:03,756 --> 00:07:05,675
So I just took you home.

80
00:07:05,758 --> 00:07:08,594
Had you not told me where you lived,
we'd be at the hospital.

81
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:11,013
I owe you big time.

82
00:07:11,097 --> 00:07:14,433
Not at all.
Thank you for this good porridge.

83
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:17,728
You don't have a bad stomach, do you?

84
00:07:17,812 --> 00:07:21,816
I make and eat porridge
when I miss my mom.

85
00:07:23,276 --> 00:07:27,572
She'd make some for me
when I didn't have an appetite.

86
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:29,824
I see.

87
00:07:29,907 --> 00:07:32,160
I learned the recipe over the shoulder.

88
00:07:33,202 --> 00:07:35,037
But it doesn't taste the same.

89
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:37,373
But it's so soothing and delicious.

90
00:07:40,418 --> 00:07:43,880
I feel good and warm in the stomach.
It relaxes me.

91
00:07:44,464 --> 00:07:47,049
I'm truly sorry for the inconvenience.

92
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:50,678
Come on. It was nearby.
It didn't even take that long.

93
00:07:50,761 --> 00:07:52,388
Remember what I said?

94
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:56,225
My wife hates it when I reek of alcohol.
She makes me sleep on the couch.

95
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:58,060
Do you only have one bedroom?

96
00:07:58,144 --> 00:08:01,481
No. There are three,
but one is for storage,

97
00:08:01,564 --> 00:08:04,609
and the study is cluttered up
with the desk and the bookshelves.

98
00:08:04,692 --> 00:08:07,195
By the way, how did we come here?

99
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:11,032
-You called a chauffeur, right?
-Of course.

100
00:08:11,115 --> 00:08:13,493
But I don't need one on my way home.
I'm sober now.

101
00:08:14,076 --> 00:08:15,620
You still shouldn't drive.

102
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:16,954
Okay.

103
00:08:18,122 --> 00:08:20,958
Did you know that protein
breaks down the alcohol,

104
00:08:21,042 --> 00:08:22,585
so it's good for hangovers?

105
00:08:22,668 --> 00:08:23,836
I heard.

106
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:27,215
So on days I drink heavily,
I have two fried eggs before going to bed.

107
00:08:27,298 --> 00:08:29,509
I like fried eggs too.

108
00:08:30,843 --> 00:08:33,513
Oh, I have some eggs.

109
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:36,182
Oh, I'll have some if you want some.

110
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:41,187
Should I fry them? I'm good at it.

111
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:42,313
You're my guest.

112
00:08:43,564 --> 00:08:45,441
You're not completely sober yet.

113
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:47,401
I like the state I'm in right now.

114
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:54,283
-Eat up before it gets cold.
-Okay.

115
00:09:04,585 --> 00:09:06,045
How much did you have?

116
00:09:06,128 --> 00:09:07,547
A ton.

117
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:10,299
I'm okay with you drinking,
but don't let it show.

118
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:11,592
Drunk men are an eyesore.

119
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:13,928
Hey, Hye-ryung.

120
00:09:17,348 --> 00:09:19,684
-"Hey"?
-Yes. Hey.

121
00:09:22,061 --> 00:09:26,232
What's wrong
with a husband calling his wife "hey"?

122
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:31,153
Can you fry me some eggs?

123
00:09:33,364 --> 00:09:35,324
-Fried eggs?
-Yes.

124
00:09:35,408 --> 00:09:36,659
Why should I?

125
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:45,459
Half-cooked or fully-cooked?

126
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,878
Do you prefer half-cooked, Song Yuan?

127
00:09:48,421 --> 00:09:51,090
Half-cooked yolks are a bit smelly,

128
00:09:51,173 --> 00:09:53,509
and fully-cooked ones are too hard,

129
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:54,885
so I like mine in-between.

130
00:09:54,969 --> 00:09:56,596
What? Me too.

131
00:10:04,312 --> 00:10:07,398
Thank you so much
for the delicious porridge.

132
00:10:08,774 --> 00:10:11,027
-Have some tangerines.
-Okay.

133
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:15,323
Do you know
when your mom looks the prettiest?

134
00:10:16,490 --> 00:10:17,950
When she's cooking.

135
00:10:18,534 --> 00:10:20,703
That's just an excuse
to make me cook for you.

136
00:10:55,363 --> 00:10:56,864
You're good at everything.

137
00:10:57,823 --> 00:11:00,201
Even kids can cook fried eggs.

138
00:11:00,284 --> 00:11:04,163
It's perfectly cooked.
Usually, the yolk breaks when you flip it.

139
00:11:06,707 --> 00:11:08,876
Why didn't you just stay in the car?

140
00:11:08,959 --> 00:11:10,419
You could've felt uncomfortable.

141
00:11:10,503 --> 00:11:13,297
You could've sat in the back.
I was sleeping anyway.

142
00:11:14,423 --> 00:11:18,886
Besides, we're not strangers.
We go to the same gym.

143
00:11:20,221 --> 00:11:22,223
Do you have a dishwasher?

144
00:11:22,306 --> 00:11:23,724
No. Why?

145
00:11:23,808 --> 00:11:26,477
I should at least do the dishes.

146
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:28,062
That's what I do at home.

147
00:11:28,896 --> 00:11:31,232
-Goodness.
-Only on the helper's days off.

148
00:11:33,818 --> 00:11:35,486
There's not much to do anyway.

149
00:11:36,654 --> 00:11:40,866
Are all men these days
as kind and sweet as you, Xiexian?

150
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:43,285
-That's a compliment, right?
-Of course.

151
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:46,288
My wife makes me do house chores.

152
00:11:46,372 --> 00:11:48,666
But I lived alone for a long time,
so it's nothing.

153
00:11:49,542 --> 00:11:50,876
You're amazing.

154
00:11:52,044 --> 00:11:56,507
At times, I keep putting things off,
so I have to deal with them all at once.

155
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:59,051
When that happens,
I don't want to do any chores.

156
00:11:59,135 --> 00:12:00,177
To be honest,

157
00:12:00,261 --> 00:12:04,432
I want to be a couch potato
when I get home after work.

158
00:12:05,057 --> 00:12:06,600
Me too.

159
00:12:06,684 --> 00:12:08,227
May I ask… Never mind.

160
00:12:08,853 --> 00:12:10,980
What is it? Ask away.

161
00:12:11,063 --> 00:12:14,608
Was your marriage life happy?
Other than not being able to have kids.

162
00:12:16,193 --> 00:12:17,111
Yes.

163
00:12:17,194 --> 00:12:19,822
Do you think of him from time to time?

164
00:12:20,614 --> 00:12:22,700
I thought I had forgotten about him.

165
00:12:24,034 --> 00:12:26,078
But I saw him
at a department store recently.

166
00:12:27,079 --> 00:12:28,831
I was looking at some sportswear

167
00:12:29,748 --> 00:12:31,459
when I heard a familiar voice.

168
00:12:32,793 --> 00:12:33,961
So I turned around.

169
00:12:34,753 --> 00:12:38,090
My ex-husband and his wife were walking

170
00:12:38,883 --> 00:12:41,927
with a girl about five or six years old.

171
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:45,598
They looked happy.

172
00:12:48,392 --> 00:12:51,770
I want to make her happy.

173
00:12:51,854 --> 00:12:53,689
Tell me the truth.

174
00:12:54,523 --> 00:12:57,276
I remember putting the muffler around you.

175
00:12:57,818 --> 00:13:01,489
Did I black out right after that?
Did I not embarrass myself?

176
00:13:03,032 --> 00:13:04,325
You didn't.

177
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:08,078
What? Do you feel like you swore at me?

178
00:13:09,622 --> 00:13:12,666
Right. There's one thing.

179
00:13:14,502 --> 00:13:17,171
You could've just wrapped the muffler
around my neck once.

180
00:13:18,214 --> 00:13:20,424
But you wrapped it several times
then pulled.

181
00:13:20,508 --> 00:13:24,720
Goodness. Really? What's wrong with me?

182
00:13:26,096 --> 00:13:28,891
In a way, I'm glad you blacked out.

183
00:13:31,727 --> 00:13:33,812
That's unbelievable. How could I…

184
00:13:35,606 --> 00:13:38,442
-You're joking, right?
-I'm not.

185
00:13:43,906 --> 00:13:46,867
Can I make her laugh like this
all the time?

186
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:48,536
How did I go to the car?

187
00:13:48,619 --> 00:13:50,996
I had no choice. I dragged you.

188
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:52,748
I'm so mortified!

189
00:13:53,332 --> 00:13:55,209
I'm kidding. I didn't drag you.

190
00:13:55,292 --> 00:13:57,586
Some woman helped me carry you on my back.

191
00:14:00,422 --> 00:14:01,674
Please forget it.

192
00:14:02,591 --> 00:14:05,553
-Forget what happened tonight.
-I don't want to.

193
00:14:05,636 --> 00:14:07,805
I even served you beef porridge.

194
00:14:08,430 --> 00:14:10,015
Have you warmed up?

195
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:12,768
Your face looks much better now.

196
00:14:12,851 --> 00:14:14,645
You should pay me back.

197
00:14:14,728 --> 00:14:17,398
Lawyers hate giving free consultation
the most.

198
00:14:18,315 --> 00:14:21,527
-You too, Lawyer Pan?
-Call me by my other name.

199
00:14:21,610 --> 00:14:22,903
You too, Xiexian?

200
00:14:24,321 --> 00:14:26,824
Be my life coach from time to time.

201
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:30,995
My brother lives in Daejeon.
There's no one I can really talk to.

202
00:14:32,329 --> 00:14:33,372
Don't you have friends?

203
00:14:33,455 --> 00:14:35,165
They're all busy with their lives.

204
00:14:35,249 --> 00:14:37,751
Those who have kids
are busy child-rearing.

205
00:14:37,835 --> 00:14:41,088
Those who are still single
are busy dating or going on blind dates.

206
00:14:43,674 --> 00:14:47,177
Be my mentor. My life mentor.

207
00:14:51,807 --> 00:14:53,559
It's been ages since we last clubbed!

208
00:14:54,351 --> 00:14:56,604
How long has it been?

209
00:14:56,687 --> 00:14:58,564
It's been over a year.

210
00:14:58,647 --> 00:15:00,232
Next time, let's exclude her.

211
00:15:00,316 --> 00:15:02,943
We can't hang out with guys
because of her.

212
00:15:03,027 --> 00:15:05,237
I won't get in the way now,
so enjoy yourselves.

213
00:15:05,321 --> 00:15:07,239
-There are many nice guys.
-Right?

214
00:15:07,323 --> 00:15:09,366
Are you sure your husband hasn't called?

215
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:10,993
Is this out of respect or neglect?

216
00:15:11,076 --> 00:15:12,494
I trained him this way.

217
00:15:12,578 --> 00:15:15,247
If he checked on me every hour,
it'd be so tiring.

218
00:15:15,331 --> 00:15:16,290
I'm not a housewife.

219
00:15:16,373 --> 00:15:19,835
Does he know any fellow lawyers
who are bachelors?

220
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:23,756
The younger girls have already
snatched the good ones away.

221
00:15:23,839 --> 00:15:25,382
And we're no match for them.

222
00:15:25,466 --> 00:15:26,675
We're not bad.

223
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:30,137
Women in their 20s and 30s are
completely different. We should know.

224
00:15:30,971 --> 00:15:35,184
Back when I was in my twenties,
I could hit a tennis ball with my butt.

225
00:15:36,852 --> 00:15:39,521
Gosh. I need to snatch
a younger guy like Hye-ryung did.

226
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:43,233
She's different from us.
She's a celebrity. That's a privilege.

227
00:15:43,317 --> 00:15:46,111
None of that matters anymore
now that I'm married.

228
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:48,030
I've lost so much after getting married.

229
00:15:48,113 --> 00:15:50,324
In every gain, there is a loss.

230
00:15:50,908 --> 00:15:52,952
You're too greedy, Hye-ryung.

231
00:15:53,035 --> 00:15:57,665
That's true. Those who have everything
tend to be greedier.

232
00:15:58,415 --> 00:15:59,917
Don't see me out. It's cold.

233
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:03,003
Thank you so much for today.

234
00:16:03,504 --> 00:16:05,506
You made me laugh a lot.

235
00:16:05,589 --> 00:16:07,049
I'm fun, aren't I?

236
00:16:07,132 --> 00:16:10,052
Thank you for the food.
That was the best beef porridge ever.

237
00:16:10,135 --> 00:16:11,387
I'll never forget it.

238
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:14,890
Tell me when you crave it again.
I'll bring some in a thermos.

239
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:18,936
Don't drink with anyone else but me.

240
00:16:19,603 --> 00:16:23,190
I won't. Thanks to you,
I know exactly how much I can drink.

241
00:16:23,857 --> 00:16:25,693
-Good night.
-Good night.

242
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:51,677
Wait.

243
00:17:06,066 --> 00:17:07,818
I have no regrets

244
00:17:08,652 --> 00:17:12,740
other than what I did
to you and your daughter.

245
00:17:13,699 --> 00:17:15,784
I will meet with you
and ask for forgiveness.

246
00:17:15,868 --> 00:17:18,829
Did those two know each other
from the get-go?

247
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:23,917
Are they in-laws now?

248
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:25,961
Do you expect me to explain everything?

249
00:17:26,045 --> 00:17:28,964
About their ill-fated relationship
and their children?

250
00:17:29,923 --> 00:17:31,925
Why are you yelling at me?

251
00:17:32,009 --> 00:17:34,053
-I can't even ask?
-Don't talk to me.

252
00:17:34,136 --> 00:17:37,056
You're so coldhearted.

253
00:17:37,639 --> 00:17:39,058
