505
00:34:16,095 --> 00:34:17,889
-That one, please.
-Okay.

506
00:34:18,806 --> 00:34:20,433
How many candles do you need?

507
00:34:22,143 --> 00:34:23,394
Twenty-eight, please.

508
00:35:26,415 --> 00:35:30,962
MANAGER KIM

509
00:35:35,591 --> 00:35:36,926
Hello?

510
00:35:37,718 --> 00:35:40,346
Hello? Mi?

511
00:35:40,972 --> 00:35:42,056
Hello.

512
00:35:44,100 --> 00:35:45,810
Can we talk?

513
00:35:45,893 --> 00:35:46,853
Yes.

514
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:48,354
Are you in LA?

515
00:35:49,564 --> 00:35:50,606
No.

516
00:35:51,941 --> 00:35:53,276
I'm back in Korea.

517
00:35:53,359 --> 00:35:55,528
-Where are you?
-At home.

518
00:35:55,611 --> 00:35:56,571
The same apartment?

519
00:35:57,446 --> 00:35:59,699
-Yes.
-I'll be right there.

520
00:35:59,782 --> 00:36:03,286
It'll take about 50 minutes.
I'm in Bundang for horseback riding.

521
00:36:04,579 --> 00:36:05,496
Okay.

522
00:36:38,154 --> 00:36:41,324
-Just us again?
-Yes. Your dad's gone horseback riding.

523
00:36:42,325 --> 00:36:44,785
-Doesn't he look handsome?
-He's the best.

524
00:36:45,286 --> 00:36:47,747
You should go horse-riding too
when you go to middle school.

525
00:36:47,830 --> 00:36:50,124
-But I'm scared.
-Don't be.

526
00:36:50,208 --> 00:36:51,834
He's never fallen off so far.

527
00:36:51,918 --> 00:36:53,628
I'm scared of horses.

528
00:36:54,128 --> 00:36:56,756
They have humongous eyes
and gigantic faces.

529
00:37:00,134 --> 00:37:01,969
Is there no meat?

530
00:37:03,137 --> 00:37:04,805
It's beef brisket fried rice.

531
00:37:08,434 --> 00:37:11,979
Even when you're having just fried rice,
don't eat it straight out of the pan.

532
00:37:12,063 --> 00:37:13,898
Put it in a pretty bowl.

533
00:37:13,981 --> 00:37:15,733
It makes it look nicer.

534
00:37:15,816 --> 00:37:17,318
Yes. It looks tastier.

535
00:37:17,401 --> 00:37:19,820
Teach your daughter to do the same thing.

536
00:37:19,904 --> 00:37:22,490
What if I have a son?
What if I don't get married?

537
00:37:22,573 --> 00:37:25,076
Even sons need to know these things.

538
00:37:25,159 --> 00:37:27,745
And I'm certain you will get married.

539
00:37:27,828 --> 00:37:31,082
-Why?
-Those who say they won't always do.

540
00:37:31,165 --> 00:37:33,042
Did you not want to?

541
00:37:33,793 --> 00:37:35,586
-No.
-Why?

542
00:37:36,379 --> 00:37:37,213
No reason.

543
00:37:37,296 --> 00:37:39,840
What do you mean?
You must've had a reason.

544
00:37:39,924 --> 00:37:42,635
You first. Why do you
not want to get married?

545
00:37:45,471 --> 00:37:47,598
I will.
I can't think of any reason not to.

546
00:37:49,767 --> 00:37:50,935
What about you?

547
00:37:51,018 --> 00:37:53,062
I wondered,

548
00:37:53,562 --> 00:37:56,440
"Will marriage make me happy?"
I wouldn't know. I was single.

549
00:37:56,524 --> 00:37:58,276
So how is it?

550
00:37:58,359 --> 00:38:02,321
I'm so happy to be living
with you and your dad.

551
00:38:02,405 --> 00:38:03,864
I'm glad I got married.

552
00:38:05,992 --> 00:38:08,536
I should marry someone like Dad.

553
00:38:10,246 --> 00:38:13,499
It'll be hard for an average man
to satisfy your dad.

554
00:38:13,582 --> 00:38:15,001
He should satisfy me first.

555
00:38:20,089 --> 00:38:21,841
The doors are closing.

556
00:38:46,574 --> 00:38:47,408
PULL THE HANDLE

557
00:39:14,894 --> 00:39:15,728
Mi.

558
00:39:32,620 --> 00:39:33,662
Where were you?

559
00:39:35,414 --> 00:39:37,166
I went down to my car.

560
00:39:43,381 --> 00:39:45,716
I can't go anywhere dressed like this.

561
00:39:46,550 --> 00:39:47,385
Have a seat.

562
00:40:04,360 --> 00:40:06,487
-Is it your birthday today?
-Yes.

563
00:40:31,137 --> 00:40:32,596
You should've called me sooner.

564
00:40:34,265 --> 00:40:37,268
-When did you come back?
-The day I told you I would.

565
00:40:41,981 --> 00:40:45,776
You should've called in the morning.
I would've booked us a restaurant.

566
00:40:54,493 --> 00:40:56,996
-Were you sick?
-Not my body.

567
00:40:58,831 --> 00:41:01,417
None of the medicines you gave me

568
00:41:02,209 --> 00:41:03,919
was for the pain in my heart.

569
00:41:06,547 --> 00:41:08,674
You should've consulted me.

570
00:41:08,757 --> 00:41:10,342
I'll do as you say.

571
00:41:17,099 --> 00:41:18,058
I missed you.

572
00:41:20,060 --> 00:41:21,437
I did.

573
00:41:24,815 --> 00:41:26,192
I just came…

574
00:42:23,874 --> 00:42:26,126
It's wintertime.
Wouldn't it be cold for him?

575
00:42:26,210 --> 00:42:28,045
He's healthy, so he'll stay warm.

576
00:42:28,629 --> 00:42:30,005
He says it's cool and nice.

577
00:42:30,589 --> 00:42:32,383
I don't get it.

578
00:42:32,466 --> 00:42:33,842
Once you get married,

579
00:42:33,926 --> 00:42:36,679
do this for your husband,
and he'll love it.

580
00:42:37,263 --> 00:42:40,182
How could you do this every single day?
You're incredible.

581
00:42:40,266 --> 00:42:42,726
Your dad's devoted himself to our family.

582
00:42:42,810 --> 00:42:44,436
He's a good dad and a good husband.

583
00:42:44,520 --> 00:42:46,605
A wonderful son and an excellent doctor.

584
00:42:56,073 --> 00:42:57,908
I'm the best wife in the world.

585
00:43:24,226 --> 00:43:26,937
-You're not asleep, are you?
-No.

586
00:43:32,526 --> 00:43:33,861
Don't you smell soap?

587
00:43:34,445 --> 00:43:36,655
I don't know. I have a stuffy nose.

588
00:43:38,157 --> 00:43:41,285
-Do you have a cold?
-My limbs are aching.

589
00:43:41,368 --> 00:43:43,245
I think I'm coming down with a cold.

590
00:43:44,121 --> 00:43:45,706
I shouldn't get it.

591
00:43:45,789 --> 00:43:48,334
Can you crank up the heat? I'm cold.

592
00:43:48,417 --> 00:43:49,877
Do you have a fever?

593
00:43:51,170 --> 00:43:53,589
-Do we have any black herbal tea?
-I finished it.

594
00:43:54,548 --> 00:43:57,885
I had some and gave some to the staff.
You know I get cold easily.

595
00:44:04,016 --> 00:44:05,851
You should sleep in the living room.

596
00:44:07,436 --> 00:44:09,146
I really can't get sick.

597
00:44:09,229 --> 00:44:11,357
-But I can?
-I have to go on air.

598
00:44:13,859 --> 00:44:16,987
Okay? Do you really want me
to sleep in the living room?

599
00:44:17,655 --> 00:44:20,491
-Do I have to leave?
-It's better than getting both of us sick.

600
00:44:30,042 --> 00:44:31,919
You should've been careful like me.

601
00:44:40,552 --> 00:44:42,346
Take out a thick blanket.

602
00:44:42,930 --> 00:44:45,557
-Should I do it for you?
-Forget it.

603
00:45:07,371 --> 00:45:08,872
Don't go to the gym tomorrow.

604
00:45:11,875 --> 00:45:13,127
Good night.

605
00:45:28,976 --> 00:45:30,936
Did Mr. Kim stop by?

606
00:45:31,019 --> 00:45:32,104
Yes.

607
00:45:34,398 --> 00:45:36,066
-Look at this.
-What is that?

608
00:45:36,150 --> 00:45:37,734
Dongmi's kindergarten uniform.

609
00:45:38,235 --> 00:45:42,489
-You're sending Dongmi to kindergarten?
-Yes. A kindergarten for dogs.

610
00:45:44,116 --> 00:45:47,035
-You're joking, right?
-I'm not.

611
00:45:48,287 --> 00:45:49,663
Look at this hat.

612
00:45:53,000 --> 00:45:53,959
This is her backpack.

613
00:45:54,042 --> 00:45:56,420
We need to pack her snacks and kibble.

614
00:45:57,004 --> 00:45:57,838
Goodness.

615
00:45:58,922 --> 00:46:02,134
Let me borrow Byeol-hui's words
and say, "Ridiculous."

616
00:46:02,217 --> 00:46:03,177
A dog kindergarten?

617
00:46:03,260 --> 00:46:05,179
She needs to go there.

618
00:46:05,262 --> 00:46:07,598
She needs to make friends and exercise.

619
00:46:07,681 --> 00:46:10,851
You have too much money. Unbelievable.

620
00:46:10,934 --> 00:46:12,936
It's no different from the elderly

621
00:46:13,020 --> 00:46:15,063
going to culture centers
or community centers.

622
00:46:15,147 --> 00:46:17,566
Dogs can feel lonely and bored as well.

623
00:46:17,649 --> 00:46:20,152
-How much is the tuition?
-You don't need to know that.

624
00:46:20,736 --> 00:46:23,322
We live in a strange world these days.

625
00:46:23,405 --> 00:46:25,407
So? When will she start attending?

626
00:46:25,491 --> 00:46:28,744
Just pick up the phone.
And change the ringtone. It's too noisy.

627
00:46:33,874 --> 00:46:36,919
Sa-hyeon, How surprising.
Why are you calling at this hour?

628
00:46:37,794 --> 00:46:42,007
Mom, do you have
any jujube ginger tea at home?

629
00:46:45,177 --> 00:46:47,763
There must be some extract in the freezer.

630
00:46:48,347 --> 00:46:50,516
What's wrong with your voice?
Are you sick?

631
00:46:50,599 --> 00:46:52,017
I have a cold and fever.

632
00:46:52,100 --> 00:46:55,395
Oh, dear. You must've overworked yourself.

633
00:46:55,479 --> 00:46:57,231
Do you have anything at home?

634
00:46:57,314 --> 00:46:59,399
Didn't Dr. Cho send you
some black herbal tea?

635
00:46:59,483 --> 00:47:02,277
-We finished it.
-What should I do?

636
00:47:02,361 --> 00:47:05,906
Ask Hye-ryung to make you
some warm honey tea.

637
00:47:05,989 --> 00:47:08,825
I had bought all the ingredients.
Did she not make you any?

638
00:47:08,909 --> 00:47:11,036
It's too late right now.

639
00:47:11,119 --> 00:47:13,080
She just needs to boil it for two hours.

640
00:47:13,163 --> 00:47:17,417
Could you have Mr. Kim
bring some over tomorrow?

641
00:47:17,501 --> 00:47:20,212
Okay. Will you be able to go to work?

642
00:47:22,381 --> 00:47:24,216
I have a trial scheduled for tomorrow.

643
00:47:24,299 --> 00:47:27,386
Then you should go to bed. Good night.

644
00:47:30,097 --> 00:47:33,475
Did you have to make such a big deal
out of a simple cold?

645
00:47:34,977 --> 00:47:36,144
What would that make me?

646
00:47:36,228 --> 00:47:39,231
She might think I don't care
whether her husband's sick.

647
00:47:39,314 --> 00:47:41,316
Aren't you even worried about me?

648
00:47:41,400 --> 00:47:43,527
You might feel better tomorrow.

649
00:47:43,610 --> 00:47:46,488
Having some hot bean sprout and rice soup
in the morning

650
00:47:46,572 --> 00:47:48,198
could make you feel better.

651
00:47:53,036 --> 00:47:54,162
You're so thoughtless.

652
00:47:56,331 --> 00:47:57,916
Grow up. Quit acting like a baby.

653
00:47:59,126 --> 00:48:01,712
-"Baby"?
-In that feeble voice…

654
00:48:01,795 --> 00:48:04,881
If I were you, I wouldn't tell my parents
so they won't get worried.

655
00:48:04,965 --> 00:48:06,758
But I need to get well soon.

656
00:48:06,842 --> 00:48:09,595
You could call Dr. Cho tomorrow
and ask him to send you some.

657
00:48:09,678 --> 00:48:12,639
After hearing her beloved youngest son
caught a cold,

658
00:48:12,723 --> 00:48:14,850
she won't be able to sleep well.

659
00:48:25,068 --> 00:48:27,446
Gosh, she's so inconsiderate.

660
00:48:29,364 --> 00:48:30,741
She's so selfish.

661
00:48:33,702 --> 00:48:36,038
Why didn't you change?

662
00:48:36,121 --> 00:48:37,497
I was too lazy.

663
00:48:38,206 --> 00:48:41,460
-I guess you guys didn't drink.
-We just chatted.

664
00:48:41,543 --> 00:48:43,503
At times, men are chattier than women.

665
00:48:44,087 --> 00:48:45,339
Tell me about it.

666
00:48:45,422 --> 00:48:47,549
I'm sure you were just as chatty.

667
00:48:50,969 --> 00:48:53,513
Gosh, I'm exhausted.

668
00:48:54,931 --> 00:48:57,225
Chatting is more exhausting
than horseback riding.

669
00:48:58,143 --> 00:49:01,021
I used up all the energy
from horseback riding on chatting.

670
00:49:01,104 --> 00:49:03,023
You should've left first.

671
00:49:03,106 --> 00:49:05,233
I had to maintain my connections.

672
00:49:05,317 --> 00:49:07,778
There was one chairman
who hadn't come in a long time.

673
00:49:08,278 --> 00:49:10,238
Are you too tired to embrace your wife?

674
00:49:10,864 --> 00:49:12,949
I put aside some energy for that.

675
00:49:58,036 --> 00:50:01,289
Song Yuan, I'm sick.

676
00:50:24,813 --> 00:50:28,150
I didn't get married
to be treated like this.

677
00:50:30,902 --> 00:50:33,447
-Is he coughing?
-No, not quite.

678
00:50:33,530 --> 00:50:34,948
It's the onset of the flu.

679
00:50:35,031 --> 00:50:37,492
I'll concoct some medicine
instead of black herbal tea,

680
00:50:37,576 --> 00:50:38,744
in individual packets.

681
00:50:38,827 --> 00:50:41,663
Okay. Thank you.

682
00:50:41,747 --> 00:50:43,373
Dongmi.

683
00:50:44,166 --> 00:50:45,250
Is Mr. Kim here?

684
00:50:45,333 --> 00:50:47,294
He's on his way here
from Sa-hyeon's office.

685
00:50:47,878 --> 00:50:48,962
His wife is of no use.

686
00:50:49,045 --> 00:50:51,131
Having a wife doesn't mean
he won't get sick.

687
00:50:51,715 --> 00:50:53,967
-Jun-jae.
-Yes?

688
00:50:55,343 --> 00:50:58,430
Pack some kibble and snacks
in this bag for Dongmi.

689
00:50:58,513 --> 00:51:00,682
-Okay.
-But not too much.

690
00:51:00,766 --> 00:51:02,976
Dongmi's treated better than most people.

691
00:51:03,643 --> 00:51:04,603
I know.

692
00:51:07,397 --> 00:51:09,357
Puppies,

693
00:51:09,441 --> 00:51:11,485
when your new friend hops on, don't bark.

694
00:51:11,568 --> 00:51:15,197
Say, "Welcome!"
Don't scare the new student.

695
00:51:16,990 --> 00:51:18,825
Really?

696
00:51:18,909 --> 00:51:23,538
Let's go to kindergarten.
Hold on, Dongmi. Goodness.

697
00:51:23,622 --> 00:51:24,790
Goodness.

698
00:51:26,333 --> 00:51:27,584
Hello.

699
00:51:28,710 --> 00:51:30,212
I'm Audrey.

700
00:51:31,254 --> 00:51:33,548
So you're Dongmi.

701
00:51:34,216 --> 00:51:36,051
My, how pretty you are!

702
00:51:36,134 --> 00:51:37,302
Goodness.

703
00:51:38,136 --> 00:51:42,349
Goodness, you look so young.

704
00:51:42,432 --> 00:51:45,685
But it looks like
you've already had puppies.

705
00:51:46,478 --> 00:51:47,854
Is she married or not?

706
00:51:48,688 --> 00:51:52,275
Sir, did you pack her snacks and kibble?

707
00:51:53,652 --> 00:51:57,572
All right. Say bye to Daddy.

708
00:51:58,073 --> 00:51:59,699
Bye.

709
00:51:59,783 --> 00:52:01,701
-What is it?
-Next time.

710
00:52:01,785 --> 00:52:02,869
What do you mean?

711
00:52:02,953 --> 00:52:05,914
She's not feeling too well today.
I'll send her next time.

712
00:52:05,997 --> 00:52:09,668
We have a nurse's office. Don't worry.

713
00:52:09,751 --> 00:52:12,546
-No.
-But you've registered.

714
00:52:12,629 --> 00:52:14,339
I didn't do it.

715
00:52:14,422 --> 00:52:18,343
In any case, aren't you Mr. Pan Mun-ho?

716
00:52:18,426 --> 00:52:20,887
We received money under that name.

717
00:52:20,971 --> 00:52:23,557
-I won't send her.
-Why not?

718
00:52:26,226 --> 00:52:28,895
You look scary. She'll be so scared.

719
00:52:28,979 --> 00:52:32,440
What did you say?
What's wrong with my face?

720
00:52:32,524 --> 00:52:34,025
Wait, grandpa!

721
00:52:36,027 --> 00:52:38,697
-"Grandpa"?
-You're being too rude.

722
00:52:38,780 --> 00:52:40,323
Have you looked into the mirror?

723
00:52:40,407 --> 00:52:42,367
I'm not a grandpa.

724
00:52:43,243 --> 00:52:44,578
I'm her dad.

725
00:52:44,661 --> 00:52:46,955
Whatever. I don't care what you are.

726
00:52:47,038 --> 00:52:49,165
How dare you judge my face?

727
00:52:49,249 --> 00:52:52,961
Forget it. I don't need a refund,
so just leave.

728
00:52:53,545 --> 00:52:55,297
How can I when my pride is hurt?

729
00:52:55,380 --> 00:52:56,423
Suit yourself.

730
00:52:59,301 --> 00:53:01,303
Do you never look into the mirror?

731
00:53:01,386 --> 00:53:04,723
You're going to scare her.
She'll have a fit.

732
00:53:06,099 --> 00:53:08,685
You're giving me a fit.

733
00:53:10,312 --> 00:53:11,855
My heart aches.

734
00:53:12,355 --> 00:53:15,233
My puppies love me so much, you know?

735
00:53:15,317 --> 00:53:17,986
Look at them. They're not even barking.

736
00:53:18,069 --> 00:53:19,321
They're too intimidated.

737
00:53:20,405 --> 00:53:21,865
-Wait.
-Stop.

738
00:53:22,449 --> 00:53:23,825
Please don't cause a scene.

739
00:53:23,909 --> 00:53:27,621
Ma'am, no one has ever humiliated me
like this before.

740
00:53:27,704 --> 00:53:31,374
How could he think of judging
someone's appearance and hurting them?

741
00:53:32,626 --> 00:53:35,629
What about him? What about your husband?

742
00:53:35,712 --> 00:53:39,466
He and I are just the same
when it comes to looks.

743
00:53:39,549 --> 00:53:42,844
He tends to talk like that.

744
00:53:45,764 --> 00:53:47,641
She is frightening.

745
00:53:47,724 --> 00:53:49,351
All right. You need to bounce.

746
00:53:49,434 --> 00:53:51,603
-One, two, three.
-Two, three.

747
00:53:51,686 --> 00:53:53,897
-That's good.
-Hold the reins.

748
00:53:53,980 --> 00:53:56,858
Relax your legs and lower your heels.

749
00:53:56,942 --> 00:53:58,193
Lower them. Okay.

750
00:53:58,276 --> 00:53:59,694
-Are you comfortable?
-Yes.

751
00:54:01,905 --> 00:54:04,991
Dong-mi, sing a song for me.

752
00:54:07,911 --> 00:54:13,875
A small leaf falls

753
00:54:14,668 --> 00:54:19,547
From a thin branch

754
00:54:20,757 --> 00:54:27,222
Even if you are a tree

755
00:54:27,305 --> 00:54:31,977
Even if I'm a leaf

756
00:54:33,728 --> 00:54:38,191
-Nothing is left
-This is fun.

757
00:54:38,274 --> 00:54:39,401
You're doing great.

758
00:54:40,151 --> 00:54:45,198
-Are you getting the hang of it?
-In our relationship

759
00:54:46,700 --> 00:54:51,788
Even if you are a tree

760
00:54:51,871 --> 00:54:58,003
-Don't lift the reins. Do this.
-And I am a leaf

761
00:55:31,745 --> 00:55:38,710
HEAD OF DEPARTMENT, THEATER AND FILM
PARK HAE-RYUN

762
00:57:04,629 --> 00:57:06,422
You slept in for once.

763
00:57:07,298 --> 00:57:08,133
Goodness.

764
00:57:09,050 --> 00:57:10,593
I couldn't sleep well.

765
00:57:12,053 --> 00:57:15,348
-Are you feeling ill?
-Remember that kindergarten teacher?

766
00:57:15,890 --> 00:57:17,684
Audrey or something.

767
00:57:17,767 --> 00:57:20,228
-Yes?
-I saw her in my dreams.

768
00:57:20,311 --> 00:57:23,356
She glared and chased me around.
I was scared to death.

769
00:57:24,232 --> 00:57:25,483
Don't be so dramatic.

770
00:57:25,567 --> 00:57:27,444
I should be careful today.

771
00:57:29,112 --> 00:57:31,990
-How's Sa-hyeon doing?
-He's doing much better now.

772
00:57:32,073 --> 00:57:34,701
My family never gets sick under my care.

773
00:57:34,784 --> 00:57:37,412
When he ate my food,
he never caught a cold.

774
00:57:37,495 --> 00:57:39,789
I'll give you that.

775
00:57:40,498 --> 00:57:41,332
So Ye-jeong.

776
00:57:42,375 --> 00:57:44,127
You do take great care of your family.

777
00:57:44,836 --> 00:57:45,670
What else?

778
00:57:49,299 --> 00:57:50,467
What else?

779
00:57:51,468 --> 00:57:52,927
I have to pee.

780
00:58:35,929 --> 00:58:38,598
I picked it out myself.
Exchange it if you want.

781
00:58:49,275 --> 00:58:51,236
-Good morning, sir.
-Good morning.

782
00:58:57,116 --> 00:58:58,201
MY LOVE

783
00:58:58,284 --> 00:59:01,329
I love it so much. I "wuv" you.

784
00:59:08,127 --> 00:59:09,170
Huh?

785
00:59:09,254 --> 00:59:10,421
You're here early.

786
00:59:10,505 --> 00:59:12,465
A variety show producer wanted to see me.

787
00:59:12,549 --> 00:59:15,176
-Are you interested?
-No, I'm too busy.

788
00:59:15,260 --> 00:59:17,095
But we should at least talk.

789
00:59:18,096 --> 00:59:19,973
Gosh, isn't that new?

790
00:59:20,640 --> 00:59:22,183
When did you buy it?

791
00:59:22,267 --> 00:59:25,061
My husband bought it for me
as a surprise gift.

792
00:59:25,144 --> 00:59:28,690
Gosh, I'm so jealous.
You have a great husband.

793
00:59:30,400 --> 00:59:32,485
Mine has nothing to offer
but his young age.

794
00:59:32,569 --> 00:59:35,029
My husband wasn't good
at these things too at first.

795
00:59:35,113 --> 00:59:38,950
But after some time, his love grew,
and he became sweeter.

796
00:59:41,578 --> 00:59:42,745
Hey.

797
00:59:44,914 --> 00:59:46,833
-Did you just finish?
-Yes.

798
00:59:46,916 --> 00:59:48,710
I thought I'd see you at this hour.

799
00:59:50,169 --> 00:59:52,839
-Maybe I'll just skip it.
-Don't do that.

800
00:59:52,922 --> 00:59:54,716
You're going to have dinner, right?

801
00:59:55,758 --> 00:59:58,094
There's a place nearby
that offers a great barbecue.

802
01:00:07,103 --> 01:00:10,481
-I was sick.
-Oh, no. Was it because of that night?

803
01:00:10,565 --> 01:00:13,192
No. It's because I didn't drink
any burdock tea.

804
01:00:13,276 --> 01:00:16,946
Having a glass of your warm burdock tea
before working out kept me nice and warm.

805
01:00:17,780 --> 01:00:19,157
But I had to drink cold water.

806
01:00:21,909 --> 01:00:23,536
I fell ill from overworking myself.

807
01:00:24,996 --> 01:00:26,205
Did you skip work?

808
01:00:26,289 --> 01:00:28,708
I had a trial to attend, so I had to go.

809
01:00:28,791 --> 01:00:32,045
Are you okay now?
You shouldn't overwork yourself.

810
01:00:33,713 --> 01:00:35,173
I'm here because I am.

811
01:00:35,673 --> 01:00:37,425
I was worried.

812
01:00:38,718 --> 01:00:40,136
I kept wondering.

813
01:00:40,219 --> 01:00:41,346
About what?

814
01:00:41,429 --> 01:00:43,723
If I had made a mistake that night.

815
01:00:43,806 --> 01:00:46,559
Gosh. You didn't.

816
01:00:46,643 --> 01:00:49,646
It's my fault for ordering alcohol,
not knowing you can't drink.

817
01:00:49,729 --> 01:00:51,230
I could've just drank alone.

818
01:00:51,314 --> 01:00:53,191
At least we had fun.

819
01:00:55,943 --> 01:00:58,905
My wife doesn't let me work out
in the evening.

820
01:00:58,988 --> 01:01:01,741
She says it'll get in the way
of work and gatherings.

821
01:01:02,325 --> 01:01:03,576
That's true.

822
01:01:03,660 --> 01:01:05,286
What have you been up to?

823
01:01:05,370 --> 01:01:09,791
Once I do my work, clean the house,

824
01:01:09,874 --> 01:01:12,210
buy groceries, and work out,
it's already nighttime.

825
01:01:12,293 --> 01:01:13,670
Didn't you wonder about me?

826
01:01:13,753 --> 01:01:16,798
I was worried about you instead.

827
01:01:16,881 --> 01:01:19,258
How did you come today
if she didn't let you?

828
01:01:19,342 --> 01:01:20,968
Because I had no plans.

829
01:01:21,636 --> 01:01:24,931
Then you should've gone straight home
and spent time with your wife.

830
01:01:25,014 --> 01:01:26,265
Have dinner with her.

831
01:01:26,349 --> 01:01:29,852
We only see each other sleeping
during the weekdays.

832
01:01:29,936 --> 01:01:32,814
When I go to work in the morning,
she's fast asleep.

833
01:01:34,565 --> 01:01:36,359
-Here's your food.
-Thank you.

834
01:01:39,362 --> 01:01:41,072
Gosh, I want a drink.

835
01:01:41,155 --> 01:01:43,991
Go ahead. Don't mind me.

836
01:01:44,075 --> 01:01:46,411
-It's okay.
-At least a glass of wine.

837
01:01:46,494 --> 01:01:49,831
I don't want to drink alone
or pay for a chauffeur after one drink.

838
01:01:54,085 --> 01:01:55,795
Which cut is this?

839
01:01:55,878 --> 01:01:57,714
It's beef tongue. It's good.

840
01:02:00,550 --> 01:02:02,802
I'll skip this dish.

841
01:02:02,885 --> 01:02:05,847
I don't want a cow's tongue touching mine.

842
01:02:09,058 --> 01:02:11,436
Okay. Bye.

843
01:02:13,229 --> 01:02:16,607
That was Ji-a. She'd like to
at least go to a skating rink.

844
01:02:16,691 --> 01:02:17,859
Is that so?

845
01:02:18,568 --> 01:02:21,028
We'll go wherever our granddaughter
wants to go.

846
01:02:22,447 --> 01:02:23,740
Can you skate?

847
01:02:23,823 --> 01:02:28,244
Yes, I was pretty good when I skated
with Yu-sin years back. But now…

848
01:02:28,327 --> 01:02:31,122
Right. We shouldn't break our bones.

849
01:02:34,375 --> 01:02:36,711
-Honey!
-Hurry.

850
01:02:37,295 --> 01:02:38,880
Join us, Mom.

851
01:02:38,963 --> 01:02:40,465
U-ram, be careful.

852
01:02:41,632 --> 01:02:44,218
It would've been nicer
if Yu-sin had come too.

853
01:02:44,302 --> 01:02:45,762
He loved to skate.

854
01:02:46,345 --> 01:02:47,805
He told me.

855
01:02:47,889 --> 01:02:50,641
You guys learned to skate
when he was in elementary school.

856
01:02:50,725 --> 01:02:53,144
Yes. I figure-skated.

857
01:02:55,271 --> 01:02:58,274
-Huh? Ji-a!
-U-Ram!

858
01:02:59,776 --> 01:03:02,195
-I can't believe I ran into you.
-Me neither.

859
01:03:02,278 --> 01:03:04,363
-Are you good at skating?
-Goodness.

860
01:03:04,447 --> 01:03:05,990
Look at them having fun.

861
01:03:15,416 --> 01:03:18,795
-Even your husband's here.
-Yes, we all came together.

862
01:03:19,378 --> 01:03:21,547
My husband went to an impromptu gathering.

863
01:03:23,341 --> 01:03:25,009
My parents-in-law are over there.

864
01:03:26,385 --> 01:03:27,804
I should go say hello.

865
01:03:29,514 --> 01:03:31,724
-She must've met a friend.
-She did.

866
01:03:32,725 --> 01:03:35,102
It's great to be back.

867
01:03:35,186 --> 01:03:37,522
This place has changed quite a bit.

868
01:03:48,324 --> 01:03:49,575
Did you sleep well?

869
01:03:49,659 --> 01:03:50,701
Put on your seatbelt.

870
01:03:53,162 --> 01:03:55,122
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

871
01:03:58,584 --> 01:04:01,754
-Aren't you cold?
-No. I'm dressed warmly.

872
01:04:04,382 --> 01:04:06,467
This is the writer of my radio program.

873
01:04:06,551 --> 01:04:08,803
Hello. Please stay seated.

874
01:04:08,886 --> 01:04:10,638
-It's okay.
-And this is her husband.

875
01:04:11,222 --> 01:04:13,099
Hello, I'm Park Hae-ryun.

876
01:04:13,182 --> 01:04:15,184
Goodness. It's nice to meet you.

877
01:04:15,768 --> 01:04:17,770
You seem like a wonderful couple.

878
01:04:17,854 --> 01:04:21,524
Her youngest son and Ji-a
were in the same class in first grade.

879
01:04:21,607 --> 01:04:23,818
-You must've had him late.
-I did.

880
01:04:24,318 --> 01:04:25,611
Please have a seat.

881
01:04:25,695 --> 01:04:28,239
-Let's go have some tea.
-Lunch would be better.

882
01:04:28,823 --> 01:04:30,616
-Should we?
-Sure.

883
01:04:52,305 --> 01:04:53,556
Yu-sin.

884
01:04:55,266 --> 01:04:57,810
I don't expect anything from you.

885
01:04:58,728 --> 01:05:02,940
I'm content with seeing you like this.

886
01:05:11,407 --> 01:05:12,742
So don't feel pressured.

887
01:05:14,869 --> 01:05:16,162
But I can't help but feel…

888
01:05:16,829 --> 01:05:18,748
If you tell me to leave,

889
01:05:19,665 --> 01:05:20,666
I will.

890
01:06:00,081 --> 01:06:02,208
Let's go.
I had Secretary Yoo buy us tickets.

891
01:06:02,291 --> 01:06:05,920
-When's the flight?
-We have 30 minutes to get your passport.

892
01:06:06,879 --> 01:06:07,964
-How many?
-Four.

893
01:06:08,047 --> 01:06:10,174
Don't bother to change me.
I'll never change.

894
01:06:10,257 --> 01:06:15,137
Since I want you guys to be honest,
I should be honest with you first.

895
01:06:15,221 --> 01:06:16,597
Is it still ongoing?

896
01:06:16,681 --> 01:06:19,642
Nothing should be for free
which is also the case this time.

897
01:06:19,725 --> 01:06:20,851
But we all like freebies.

898
01:06:20,935 --> 01:06:25,106
If I could ever be born again,
I'd get married three times.

899
01:06:25,731 --> 01:06:27,608
-Maybe I'll shake my butt.
-Go ahead.

900
01:06:27,692 --> 01:06:30,903
Why only me though? You should do it too.

901
01:06:36,492 --> 01:06:39,120
Because the stage is where Ga-bin belongs.

902
01:06:39,203 --> 01:06:41,455
She should never leave the stage!

903
01:06:41,539 --> 01:06:44,542
I love you with all my heart

904
01:06:44,625 --> 01:06:49,422
